The paper deals with lambda calculus, which is a topic in mathematical logic and theoretical computer science. The use of complex analysis and generating functions suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. The focus on functional programming and proof assistants suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The use of algorithms and experimental data suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The study of combinatorial properties of lambda terms suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) sub-category. Finally, the focus on testing compilers and optimizing programs suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
